124
00:05:18,029 --> 00:05:22,979
Jordan Laramore asks:
“China officially has like 9 political parties

125
00:05:22,979 --> 00:05:25,669
but they vote in line with the CCP,

126
00:05:25,669 --> 00:05:27,580
what are the chances that one day

127
00:05:27,580 --> 00:05:30,279
they decide to form an opposition party?”

128
00:05:30,279 --> 00:05:31,279
Well, Jordan,

129
00:05:31,279 --> 00:05:33,880
it’s interesting you should mention the
political parties.

130
00:05:33,880 --> 00:05:35,949
A lot of people think the People’s Republic
of China

131
00:05:35,949 --> 00:05:37,600
is a one-party state.

132
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:39,330
But they’d like you to know,

133
00:05:39,330 --> 00:05:41,970
that couldn’t be further from the truth!

134
00:05:41,970 --> 00:05:44,400
China has 8 other political parties.

135
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:47,619
A lot of them even have “democratic” in
their names!

136
00:05:47,619 --> 00:05:48,710
If you say it over and over,

137
00:05:48,710 --> 00:05:50,050
it must be true.

138
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:52,680
Just like the Democratic People’s Republic
of Korea.

139
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:55,650
There’s just one small catch.

140
00:05:55,650 --> 00:05:57,419
Those 8 political parties

141
00:05:57,419 --> 00:05:59,969
are directly controlled by the Communist Party.

142
00:05:59,969 --> 00:06:02,449
It’s literally written into the constitution

143
00:06:02,449 --> 00:06:04,110
that the multi-party system

144
00:06:04,110 --> 00:06:07,819
is officially under the Communist Party’s
leadership.

145
00:06:07,819 --> 00:06:12,249
After all, it’s the “People’s Democratic
Dictatorship.”

146
00:06:12,249 --> 00:06:13,949
These 8 other parties combined make up

147
00:06:13,949 --> 00:06:18,449
less than 30% of the votes in the National
People’s Congress.

148
00:06:18,449 --> 00:06:21,649
So if they wanted to form a bloc and vote
a different way,

149
00:06:21,649 --> 00:06:23,780
they couldn’t pass any laws.

150
00:06:23,780 --> 00:06:25,979
Not because of the lack of votes though.

151
00:06:25,979 --> 00:06:27,669
Because the National People’s Congress

152
00:06:27,669 --> 00:06:29,539
has no real power.

153
00:06:29,539 --> 00:06:31,460
Its job is to give the appearance of law

154
00:06:31,460 --> 00:06:33,330
to a country where policy

155
00:06:33,330 --> 00:06:36,300
is actually decided by the Communist Party.

156
00:06:36,300 --> 00:06:39,330
So if the other parties did try to oppose
it,

157
00:06:39,330 --> 00:06:41,409
the Communist Party would just declare them

158
00:06:41,409 --> 00:06:44,809
illegal organizations and crush them.

159
00:06:44,809 --> 00:06:47,389
Not that they ever would try to oppose the
Communist Party,

160
00:06:47,389 --> 00:06:50,300
since all 8 parties are also directly controlled

161
00:06:50,300 --> 00:06:54,159
by the Communist Party’s United Front organization.

162
00:06:54,159 --> 00:06:56,139
So the chance that these 8 parties

163
00:06:56,139 --> 00:06:58,789
would one day decide to form an opposition
party...

164
00:06:58,789 --> 00:07:01,229
is zero.

165
00:07:01,229 --> 00:07:02,610
There have been people in China

166
00:07:02,610 --> 00:07:05,550
who have tried to start real opposition parties,

167
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:07,149
that aren’t controlled by the Communist
Party.

168
00:07:07,149 --> 00:07:10,669
Let’s just say, it hasn’t ended well for
them.

